[37.786373, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36mACT 2 — THE REVEAL   (~30 sec)   The kicker.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[37.786555, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “Everything you just watched came from typing this in front of my”\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;33m  “training command. No config. No instrumentation. No pipeline file.”\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;37m  $ roar run python train.py\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[40.793855, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “That's it. That's the whole integration. It was free.”\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[40.794158, "o", "\r\n"]
[43.806657, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “Free, but not fooled. Watch what happens if the tree is dirty.”\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ touch test.txt\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[43.81852, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ roar run python evaluate.py\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[44.030568, "o", "Error: Run blocked: untracked files in the working tree.\r\n\r\nroar tags every run with the current git commit SHA. Untracked\r\nfiles mean the commit alone can't explain what was on disk at\r\nrun time.\r\n\r\nUntracked files:\r\n  test.txt\r\n\r\nIf they're outputs you want kept around but not in the repo, gitignore them:\r\n  echo 'test.txt' >> .gitignore\r\n  git add .gitignore && git commit -m 'ignore outputs'\r\n\r\nIf they belong in the repo, commit them:\r\n  git add test.txt\r\n  git commit -m \"<describe your changes>\"\r\n\r\nThen retry: roar run python evaluate.py\r\n\r\nWhy: https://glaas.ai/docs/why-clean-commits\r\n"]
[44.045, "o", "\r\n"]
[47.053289, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “It won't record a run it can't pin to exact code. Everything passes”\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[47.053735, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “through the commit — that's the bottleneck. Which is why the record you're”\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;33m  “about to see is complete enough to catch what I never declared.”\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[50.06387, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36mACT 3 — PAYOFF   (~2 min)   The record surfaces what I never declared.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[0;33m  “One human act. I marked the raw dataset as containing personal data.”\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[50.064109, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ roar tag show data/raw.csv\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[50.350161, "o", "Tags on data/raw.csv:\r\n  contains_pii=present\r\n"]
[50.376145, "o", "\r\n"]
[53.380054, "o", "\u001b[0;33m  “I never said anything about the other files. Watch where it went.”\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ python taint.py\u001b[0m\r\n"]
